[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test class structures**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I could place the generated class in a subdirectory under test resources. I wonder if I should use an inner class since there's no Java file. The rule says test class files should follow a one-to-one mapping, but I'm curious if helper classes might be allowed. It's tricky since I want to ensure adequate coverage while possibly using a non-Test file, but risks are involved with that approach. There's so much to consider!\n\n**Analyzing class loading and registration**\n\nI'm wondering if using PathMatchingResourcePatternResolver with the app classloader could help search the JRT. It might find classes like java/time/*.class in the boot module, allowing me to use Class.forName(\"java.time.Clock\"). However, registering java.time classes as Spring beans could fail due to possible lack of a default constructor. I’m curious if annotatedReader.register could help with that, but the refresh process could still run into issues if a bean needs to be instantiated without a required constructor. It's quite complicated!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c10cbc4c9e09abd016a25043f5ae88190bcb32fd2cd681088\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJQRX2toeBVmUYDFx-tZPJDEj-im6Ug76F2IxNdiTJydPGuYHPGVYAO4LWC8IHP4HEHcDqRRtxUbj10rRbVF55AzPMCp47jxEopdHBF-8z-28Qj3F9tMpTpEMPQc_OTtFC7pf_uLeCsckhrzfOasW09NAfAlt94o6MnCteNlWh1D7REEVXgeamK3m-nH76fIScmUhC6Fcrmns9noylT_9M_bUMaZL3y_St1gmQOTZcTEvXgmi2iZlC6nN9OBuDd-oJC341jRkpkmthdj7bKJ8Tv9RjjHiCIrLEl2PN3EZwk1argrg1ufEj9WH69usDG_Pet6V_kUo9jzyUBVgaRUYVRP_YL8FHsrA5gQpvyVvFIt46MXXIyDNmHWvOBxMHqfhls2hgLL-NAEqlRKzAcgzrNggCz6lI6DEu9Krvf7eXWUGjjOLbH5c9mNWuYcUMPVCvB02oYjUYAx0LKyNBkAeyh4_KUi8ETrS7CUfWzauWeBHaZSBT2k4CzLnggg1N-nQ-IExSwOaIR6t1edDcNwa17t_N7znhdXK57UBIXw1F1El1sMeLidV7JBpVEvtZtoXKWUfiV-TQOgWIu5aUsJBWZWBgMWXHo7Ti8CS5nITHpiyfF6KpUeeElHv8eMqN3yp0