[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to decide if I should choose a package with an @Component. It seems like I wouldn't get an exception if I don't, but I wonder if that's strong enough. It might be better to use a dependency package that includes a known @Component from spring-context. For instance, the org.springframework.stereotype package has annotation interfaces and might already be loaded due to a Component import in my helper. However, if we remove the helper, the test only imports SpringApplication and not many other packages. But Spring Boot startup does load many Spring classes.
