ss loading and testing**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether the `.core.codec` is a dependency or if it's related to spring-core. The source package seems to have scanning issues with no beans assert. Gradle's test detection likely comes from scanning compiled classes with ASM rather than from naming conventions. I might need to consider adding a `package-info.java`, but it’s not strictly necessary. Also, I'm thinking about whether `containsBean` might trigger bean creation, given that non-lazy singletons get instantiated after a refresh.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Spring Native component scanning**\\n\\nI’m considering the component scanning in Spring Native and whether it scans `.class` resources in the native image. The test metadata should include the test class resources, which could be managed by an agent using patterns. It's important to note that we aren't compiling or running tests ourselves, as the guidelines suggested, so that's good. I might have considered using `git diff` for untracked files, but it seems unnecessary. Also, our helper is in its own package, avoiding metadata modifications.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.springframework.boot.BeanDefinitionLoader`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/BeanDefinitionLoaderTest.java`\n  - Uses public `SpringApplication` API with `setSources(Set.of(packageName))`.\n  - Runs an application from a package-name source to exercise `BeanDefinitionLoader.findPackage(...)`, including the `Class.forName(...)` call site.\n- Added helper component:\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/beandefinitionloader/BeanDefinitionLoaderPackageComponent.java`\n  - Provides a real component in an otherwise unreferenced package so package discovery has a supported classpath target.\n\nNo reachability metadata or na