[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m wondering if the "newly covered none" statement refers to the BeanDefinitionLoaderTest file existing without any coverage reported. Maybe the generated test didn’t compile? It seems like the harness ran, yet didn't necessarily fail, but resulted in no coverage. I might need to add a test that calls the public API while ensuring branch coverage. Also, using a Spring Boot jar package that isn't loaded could be a possibility, although the classloader might define all packages in the jar.
